A cyberpunk cityscape at night where thousands of tiny glowing sensors float like fireflies between towering skyscrapers, each sensor trailing thin neon-blue data streams that weave together into a massive interconnected web spanning the urban canyon. Cars on elevated highways pulse with soft orange lights as they feed data upward into the network. The buildings themselves are embedded with countless small luminous nodes, their windows reflecting the electric blue mesh overhead. Rain falls through the data streams, creating shimmering interference patterns. The perspective is from street level looking up, emphasizing the vast scale of the connected infrastructure against a deep purple sky crackling with digital aurora.
